<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1647,2034]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1827,1853]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nel &amp; Varenne" authorityYear="2012" box="[326,720,1827,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrneochalcopepla">
<emphasis box="[326,720,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Pseudopostega cyrneochalcopepla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from two males with identical collection data (
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, J. &amp; Varenne, T." box="[159,418,1863,1890]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="11 - 13" refId="ref19495" refString="Nel, J. &amp; Varenne, T. (2012 a) Pseudopostega cyrneochalcopepla n. sp., Monochroa cyrneogonella n. sp., Syncopacma cinctelloides n. sp., especes nouvelles decouvertes en Corse (Lep. Opostegidae, Gelechiidae). Oreina, 17, 11 - 13." type="journal article" year="2012">Nel &amp; Varenne 2012a</bibRefCitation>
). We studied and sequenced the 
<typeStatus box="[798,897,1864,1890]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">paratype</typeStatus>
, resulting in a full barcode, with a distance of 4.3% to its nearest neighbour, continental 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walsingham, 1908)" baseAuthorityName="Walsingham" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[628,1032,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcopepla">
<emphasis box="[628,793,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">P. chalcopepla</emphasis>
(Walsingham, 1908)
</taxonomicName>
. Despite this difference, the species was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walsingham" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[421,588,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcopepla">
<emphasis box="[421,588,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">P. chalcopepla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the virtual identical genitalia and external characters (van 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieukerken, E. J. van &amp; Doorenweerd, C. &amp; Hoare, R. J. B. &amp; Davis, D. R." box="[151,419,1971,1998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="65 - 246" refId="ref20976" refString="Nieukerken, E. J. van, Doorenweerd, C., Hoare, R. J. B. &amp; Davis, D. R. (2016) Revised classification and catalogue of global Nepticulidae and Opostegidae (Lepidoptera: Nepticuloidea). ZooKeys, 628, 65 - 246. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 628.9799." type="journal article" year="2016">
Nieukerken 
<emphasis box="[291,350,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). This was challenged by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, J. &amp; Varenne, T." box="[719,987,1971,1998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="71 - 74" refId="ref20033" refString="Nel, J. &amp; Varenne, T. (2016 c) Pseudopostega cyrneochalcopepla Nel &amp; Varenne, 2012, bona species, stat. rest., et Metzneria varennei Nel, 1997, synonyme junior de M. campicolella (Mann, 1857) (Lepidoptera, Opostegidae et Gelechiidae). Revue de l'Association Roussillonnaise d'Entomologie, 26 (2), 71 - 74." type="journal article" year="2016">Nel &amp; Varenne (2016c)</bibRefCitation>
who detailed additional morphological differences. However, after studying a larger number of specimens, we still failed to see differences. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, J. &amp; Varenne, T." lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="11 - 13" refId="ref19495" refString="Nel, J. &amp; Varenne, T. (2012 a) Pseudopostega cyrneochalcopepla n. sp., Monochroa cyrneogonella n. sp., Syncopacma cinctelloides n. sp., especes nouvelles decouvertes en Corse (Lep. Opostegidae, Gelechiidae). Oreina, 17, 11 - 13." type="journal article" year="2012">Nel &amp; Varenne (2012a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, J. &amp; Varenne, T." box="[245,316,151,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" pagination="71 - 74" refId="ref20033" refString="Nel, J. &amp; Varenne, T. (2016 c) Pseudopostega cyrneochalcopepla Nel &amp; Varenne, 2012, bona species, stat. rest., et Metzneria varennei Nel, 1997, synonyme junior de M. campicolella (Mann, 1857) (Lepidoptera, Opostegidae et Gelechiidae). Revue de l'Association Roussillonnaise d'Entomologie, 26 (2), 71 - 74." type="journal article" year="2016">2016c</bibRefCitation>
) gave the wingspan of 
<quantity box="[587,668,151,177]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
as a difference, but van 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieukerken, E. J. van &amp; Lastuvka, A. &amp; Lastuvka, Z." box="[954,1249,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" pagination="211 - 260" refId="ref20696" refString="Nieukerken, E. J. van, Lastuvka, A. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. (2004 a) Annotated catalogue of the Nepticulidae and Opostegidae (Lepidoptera: Nepticuloidea) of the Iberian Peninsula. SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia, 32 (127), 211 - 260." type="journal article" year="2004">
Nieukerken 
<emphasis box="[1094,1153,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">et al.</emphasis>
(2004a)
</bibRefCitation>
gave a range of 10.5â€“ 
<quantity box="[216,298,186,213]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
, which is hardly different. The number of pecten sensilla is another character mentioned by these authors: 
<quantity box="[248,346,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.382" metricValueMax="8.636" metricValueMin="8.128" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" unit="in" value="33.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="32.0">32â€“34 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nel &amp; Varenne" authorityYear="2012" box="[352,565,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrneochalcopepla">
<emphasis box="[352,565,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">cyrneochalcopepla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
versus 
<quantity box="[649,748,223,249]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1684" metricValueMax="1.2446" metricValueMin="1.0922" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" unit="in" value="46.0" valueMax="49.0" valueMin="43.0">43â€“49 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walsingham" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[754,891,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcopepla">
<emphasis box="[754,891,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">chalcopepla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, we examined several specimens from continental 
<collectingCountry box="[284,360,259,285]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">France</collectingCountry>
with 36â€“37 sensilla, showing a much larger range for this character. Other characters used are variable even within populations. Following van 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieukerken, E. J. van &amp; Doorenweerd, C. &amp; Hoare, R. J. B. &amp; Davis, D. R." box="[703,979,295,322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" pagination="65 - 246" refId="ref20976" refString="Nieukerken, E. J. van, Doorenweerd, C., Hoare, R. J. B. &amp; Davis, D. R. (2016) Revised classification and catalogue of global Nepticulidae and Opostegidae (Lepidoptera: Nepticuloidea). ZooKeys, 628, 65 - 246. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 628.9799." type="journal article" year="2016">
Nieukerken 
<emphasis box="[841,897,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
we prefer to keep the island populations within one species, until more is known of these and other island populations. 
<collectingCountry box="[1040,1108,331,357]" name="Iceland" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Island</collectingCountry>
populations often have large barcoding gaps to mainland populations, which taken alone is in our opinion not sufficient for species status.
</paragraph>
